urity, and was introduced into England as a given name by the Normans. A pale complexion combined with light hair was long an ideal of beauty in Europe (compare Modern English <i>fair</i>, which at first meant ‘beautiful’ and then, from the 16th century, ‘light in colouring’)."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Blanche de Beaumetz was born in 1211, in France, her father, Gilles I de Beaumetz, was 41 and her mother, Agnès de Coucy, was 37. She had at least 1 son and 2 daughters with Charles de HAMELINCOURT. She died in 1267, at the age of 56."},"et":{"1211–1267":"1211–1267","1200–1264":"1200–1264","1201–Female":"1201–Surnud","1203–1265":"1203–1265","1206–Male":"1206–Surnud","1208–1264":"1208–1264","1227–1270":"1227–1270","–1266":"–1266","1203–1271":"1203–1271","1230–1287":"1230–1287","1238–1297":"1238–1297","1430–Female":"1430–Surnud","1170–1214":"1170–1214","1175–1214":"1175–1214","1264":"1264","1238":"1238","1214":"1214","1211":"1211","1430":"1430","about 1214":"umbes 1214","Abt 1238":"umbes 1238","1297":"1297","1175":"1175","1230":"1230","1271":"1271","1270":"1270","1170":"1170","Abt 1230":"umbes 1230","1206":"1206","1227":"1227","1203":"1203","1267":"1267","1201":"1201","1266":"1266","1200":"1200","1287":"1287","1265":"1265","about 1200":"umbes 1200","1208":"1208","Hamelincourt, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France":"Hamelincourt, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1211–1267":"1211–1267","1200–1264":"1200–1264","1201–Female":"1201–Kuollut","1203–1265":"1203–1265","1206–Male":"1206–Kuollut","1208–1264":"1208–1264","1227–1270":"1227–1270","–1266":"–1266","1203–1271":"1203–1271","1230–1287":"1230–1287","1238–1297":"1238–1297","1430–Female":"1430–Kuollut","1170–1214":"1170–1214","1175–1214":"1175–1214","1264":"1264","1238":"1238","1214":"1214","1211":"1211","1430":"1430","about 1214":"noin 1214","Abt 1238":"noin 1238","1297":"1297","1175":"1175","1230":"1230","1271":"1271","1270":"1270","1170":"1170","Abt 1230":"noin 1230